section.section:
Of the nine regular members:
one member shall represent a local law enforcement agency;
one member shall represent a State's Attorney's office in the State;
one member shall represent a domestic insurer that issues private passenger automobile or commercial motor vehicle liability insurance in the State;
one member shall represent a foreign insurer that issues private passenger automobile or commercial motor vehicle liability insurance in the State;
one member shall represent the Governor's Office;
one member shall represent the National Insurance Crime Bureau or a similar organization; and
three members shall represent the public, including one member who represents a neighborhood or community association.

The Council has the following powers and duties:
to make grants from the Fund for motor vehicle theft intervention programs, as provided in § 2-703 of this subtitle;
to solicit and accept money for deposit into the Fund, to be used to carry out the purposes of this subtitle;
to establish or assist in the establishment of programs designed to reduce the incidence of vehicle theft and related crime;
to identify priorities for theft prevention strategies in the State and criteria for the Council's evaluation of recipients of assistance from the Council; and
to study and propose laws that will further prevent and deter vehicle theft and related crime.
